blog.name: alexandro-lima
blog.title: Alexandro Lima - Ilustrador
blog.description: Olá, bem vindo ao meu blog! Sou um ilustrador/arte finalista publicitário com larga experiência de mercado. Considero como seus “mestres inspiradores” Will Eisner, Jack Kirby, John Buscema e Canini. Sou um apreciador de quadrinhos, utilizo muito desta que é considerada a nona arte como fonte de referência para muitos de seus trabalhos.Mesclo trabalho à mão com vetorização e colorização digital em meus trabalhos. Realizo ilustrações, caricaturas, logotipos e pinturas. Este blog tem o objetivo de mostrar o que mais atual ando produzindo. Divulgue e opine!

summary: ϟ a strange wedding - s.s.  ______  summary:   + the reader and stephen are getting married requested by @sovereignoblivious ...
body:
ϟ a strange wedding - s.s.

______ 

summary: 

+ the reader and stephen are getting married requested by @sovereignoblivious

warnings: 

+ none

word count:

+ 450

______ 

the proposal was perfect: a fancy, french restaurant with excellent service, a quartet playing in the background that blended in with the murmur that continued on through the night, and the meals were just the right sizes, which left your stomachs feeling comfortably full.

as soon as stephen asked you to that high-end restaurant, you knew what was going to happen. you and stephen had been dating for a little of two years, and you both had discussed getting married long before your first anniversary. for a sorcerer, stephen couldn’t keep a secret.

as he got down on one knee, after you had abandoned the gorgeous dessert, the surrounding tables erupted into applause before you even opened your mouth. and without hesitation, you squealed ‘yes!’. sure stephen was an arrogant man at times, but he was working to better himself, and you loved him for that.

on the morning after the proposal, you set out to call all of your friends and family. the whole day was filled with screams, which were somewhat muted by your phone speaker, and planning. you and stephen both were excited to plan your wedding and the reception.

it took at least three months to just find the venue: a quaint, farm-like, outdoor area. it housed a gazebo, where the ceremony would take place, a wooden bridge that passed over a babbling creek, where your wedding pictures would be taken, and willow trees that matched the center-pieces. but after that, everything else fell into place.

on the day of the wedding, your stomach was filled with nothing but butterflies. walking down the aisle, with many people staring, was not something you were excited for. but you were excited for what would be waiting for you at the end. stephen decided that you should walk because “you are the more beautiful of this couple. everyone should be looking at you.”.

as soon as you met stephen’s eyes, your anxiety melted away. the spring breeze cooled your body down, and the smell of lavender and willow eased your senses. the wind also blew a few loose strands of stephen’s hair out of its gel corral. 

you had always disagreed with the phrases, “marriage is a ball-and-chain” and “marriage is a prison”. the moment you and stephen slipped the wedding bands onto each others’ fingers was the most freeing moment of your life. you no longer had to worry about finding the one because he was standing right in front of you.

you couldn’t wait to spend the rest of your life with stephen strange.

______

______
